1
00:00:01,583 --> 00:00:06,208
[insects buzzing]

2
00:00:06,291 --> 00:00:07,416
[chalk scraping]

3
00:00:07,500 --> 00:00:09,416
- This time, X equals four.

4
00:00:09,500 --> 00:00:11,125
Once we pop that
into the formula,

5
00:00:11,208 --> 00:00:12,708
finding Y
is pretty straightforward.

6
00:00:12,791 --> 00:00:13,958
- [violin playing]
- You can derive

7
00:00:14,041 --> 00:00:15,291
those coordinates up top

8
00:00:15,375 --> 00:00:17,083
and plot those points
on your graph.

9
00:00:17,166 --> 00:00:19,208
[piano and violin
playing "Love's Sorrow"]

10
00:00:19,291 --> 00:00:26,416
♪♪

11
00:00:26,500 --> 00:00:34,000
♪♪

12
00:00:34,083 --> 00:00:35,375
- [growls]

13
00:00:36,041 --> 00:00:39,333
- [roars]
- [wails]

14
00:00:39,416 --> 00:00:41,041
[sputters]

15
00:00:41,125 --> 00:00:42,625
- You need to focus, mister!

16
00:00:42,708 --> 00:00:45,625
- [groans]

17
00:00:45,708 --> 00:00:47,333
I played it note for note.

18
00:00:47,416 --> 00:00:49,250
- Yeah, like a robot
who isn't putting

19
00:00:49,333 --> 00:00:50,875
any of his heart into it!

20
00:00:53,208 --> 00:00:57,291
- Listen, does this have to be
our piece for the gala concert?

21
00:00:57,375 --> 00:00:58,250
- Oh, man, not this again.

22
00:01:03,375 --> 00:01:05,125
- All I'm saying is that we
should do something flashy,

23
00:01:05,208 --> 00:01:07,708
give 'em more of a show.
- Flashy? Meh!

24
00:01:07,791 --> 00:01:10,000
I happen to like our song.

25
00:01:10,083 --> 00:01:13,125
Don't be such a worrywart.
Come on.

26
00:01:13,208 --> 00:01:15,333
This duet is gonna
knock their socks off.

27
00:01:17,125 --> 00:01:18,416
[grunts]

28
00:01:22,083 --> 00:01:24,000
I know you won't wanna play it,

29
00:01:24,083 --> 00:01:25,375
but I don't know why.

30
00:01:27,666 --> 00:01:28,833
Something about it
spoke to me,

31
00:01:28,916 --> 00:01:31,875
like choosing it was fate.

32
00:01:36,250 --> 00:01:39,500
"Love's Joy,"
Friedrich Kreisler.

33
00:01:47,250 --> 00:01:49,875
And here, "Love's Sorrow."

34
00:01:51,083 --> 00:01:52,875
["Nanairo Symphony" playing]

35
00:01:55,750 --> 00:02:00,708
[singing in Japanese]

36
00:02:00,791 --> 00:02:09,708
♪♪

37
00:02:09,791 --> 00:02:18,541
♪♪

38
00:02:18,625 --> 00:02:26,666
♪♪

39
00:02:26,750 --> 00:02:35,541
♪♪

40
00:02:35,625 --> 00:02:45,375
♪♪

41
00:02:45,458 --> 00:02:54,250
♪♪

42
00:02:54,333 --> 00:03:03,208
♪♪

43
00:03:03,291 --> 00:03:12,041
♪♪

44
00:03:12,125 --> 00:03:20,166
♪♪

45
00:03:24,166 --> 00:03:27,208
-<i> "Love's Sorrow,"</i>
<i>Kreisler's companion piece</i>

46
00:03:27,291 --> 00:03:30,708
<i>to his earlier work for violin,</i>
<i>"Love's Joy."</i>

47
00:03:30,791 --> 00:03:34,291
<i>A bit later, Rachmaninoff</i>
<i>did his own arrangement,</i>

48
00:03:34,375 --> 00:03:37,458
<i>but for the piano.</i>
<i>That's kinda weird.</i>

49
00:03:37,541 --> 00:03:39,250
<i>I don't remember that</i>
<i>being there.</i>

50
00:03:42,875 --> 00:03:45,291
[playing "Love's Sorrow"]

51
00:03:45,375 --> 00:03:48,500
SAKI:<i> Asleep under</i>
<i>the piano again.</i>

52
00:03:50,916 --> 00:03:52,833
<i>You're going to catch a cold.</i>

53
00:03:55,041 --> 00:03:57,958
- [sighing]
-<i> Look how big you're getting.</i>

54
00:03:58,041 --> 00:03:59,458
<i>Dear Kousei.</i>

55
00:04:01,250 --> 00:04:03,250
[distorted notes playing]

56
00:04:03,333 --> 00:04:04,333
<i>This is your punishment.</i>

57
00:04:04,416 --> 00:04:08,041
<i>The piano</i>
<i>isn't responding to you.</i>

58
00:04:10,375 --> 00:04:12,166
-<i> I don't care anymore.</i>

59
00:04:12,250 --> 00:04:15,000
<i>Now I just wish you were dead!</i>

60
00:04:15,083 --> 00:04:16,666
<i>I can't hear!</i>

61
00:04:16,750 --> 00:04:19,833
<i>Help me! Mom!</i>

62
00:04:19,916 --> 00:04:21,458
KAORI:<i> I know</i>
<i>you don't want to play it,</i>

63
00:04:21,541 --> 00:04:23,833
<i>but I don't know why.</i>

64
00:04:23,916 --> 00:04:25,458
- It's simple, really.

65
00:04:25,541 --> 00:04:28,625
I can't hear this song
without thinking of my Mom.

66
00:04:34,083 --> 00:04:35,291
[gasps]

67
00:04:39,750 --> 00:04:41,375
[Koharu laughs]

68
00:04:41,458 --> 00:04:43,375
[overlapping chatter]

69
00:04:43,458 --> 00:04:44,166
[drum and flute playing]

70
00:04:44,250 --> 00:04:46,375
- [Koharu laughs]
- Hiroko,

71
00:04:46,458 --> 00:04:48,291
shouldn't I be running
the piece right now?

72
00:04:48,375 --> 00:04:50,750
- All work and no play
makes Jack a dull boy.

73
00:04:50,833 --> 00:04:52,541
A little fun
ain't gonna kill you.

74
00:04:52,625 --> 00:04:54,041
- I wanna get cotton candy!

75
00:04:54,125 --> 00:04:56,750
- Try not to barf it all up,
okay?! [sighs]

76
00:04:56,833 --> 00:04:57,333
- [chuckles]

77
00:05:02,041 --> 00:05:04,541
- Rachmaninoff's arrangement
of "Love's Sorrow," huh?

78
00:05:04,625 --> 00:05:09,250
Your Mom used to play that
all the time back in school.

79
00:05:09,333 --> 00:05:11,333
- And later on, too,

80
00:05:11,416 --> 00:05:12,750
as my lullaby.

81
00:05:12,833 --> 00:05:15,583
I think maybe...

82
00:05:15,666 --> 00:05:19,458
maybe it comes
with too much baggage.

83
00:05:19,541 --> 00:05:21,083
<i>With every measure,</i>

84
00:05:21,166 --> 00:05:23,458
<i>the old pain closes in on me.</i>

85
00:05:25,166 --> 00:05:27,083
That day in the lobby,

86
00:05:27,166 --> 00:05:30,333
my Mom, she must have
hated me, right?

87
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:35,041
- She was sick and angry,
but she was your Mom, Kousei.

88
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:38,291
Think about it.

89
00:05:38,375 --> 00:05:40,166
When you stood up for yourself,

90
00:05:40,250 --> 00:05:42,750
you grew as a performer
and a person alike.

91
00:05:42,833 --> 00:05:47,916
♪♪

92
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:49,750
[child crying]

93
00:05:49,833 --> 00:05:50,541
- Huh? Eh?

94
00:05:53,666 --> 00:05:56,250
- Ahh. Never scare Mommy
like that again, okay?

95
00:05:56,333 --> 00:05:58,916
- Ohh.
- But it does break your heart

96
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:00,416
a little bit, you know,

97
00:06:00,500 --> 00:06:02,458
watching your kid
get smaller in the distance.

98
00:06:06,583 --> 00:06:08,583
- She's my Mom...

99
00:06:08,666 --> 00:06:11,958
and I've tried so hard
to forget about her.

100
00:06:12,041 --> 00:06:14,333
Do you think she'll
ever forgive me for that?

101
00:06:18,875 --> 00:06:21,583
Is it all right
that I'm playing the piano

102
00:06:21,666 --> 00:06:23,000
even though she's gone?

103
00:06:25,875 --> 00:06:27,666
- It's better than all right.

104
00:06:27,750 --> 00:06:30,791
If you get hung up,
just pour your heart into it.

105
00:06:30,875 --> 00:06:33,625
That's what your Mom would do.

106
00:06:33,708 --> 00:06:34,916
- She would.

107
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:36,875
- Worrying won't help you
prep that piece.

108
00:06:36,958 --> 00:06:40,041
If you want it, you're gonna
have to work for it, Kousei.

109
00:06:41,416 --> 00:06:42,958
So play.
We're pianists, you know.

110
00:06:43,041 --> 00:06:45,541
It's kind of our shtick.

111
00:06:47,541 --> 00:06:48,125
- [gasps]

112
00:06:48,208 --> 00:06:50,458
- Want a candy apple?

113
00:06:53,541 --> 00:06:55,291
- Uh...
- I got it for you.

114
00:06:55,375 --> 00:06:56,166
You don't want it?
- Yeah, I'm sure they're great!

115
00:06:56,250 --> 00:06:58,541
I've just never had one before!

116
00:06:58,625 --> 00:06:59,833
No, no, no, no, no! Don't cry!
I'll eat it!

117
00:06:59,916 --> 00:07:03,666
I'll eat it right now, okay?
See? See? I'm holding it.

118
00:07:03,750 --> 00:07:05,750
HIROKO:<i> Maybe I'm being</i>
<i>too tough on him.</i>

119
00:07:05,833 --> 00:07:07,833
- Eat it.
<i>- But he's got to play,</i>

120
00:07:07,916 --> 00:07:11,500
<i>not only to grow</i>
<i>as a pianist, but also...</i>

121
00:07:11,583 --> 00:07:12,500
KOUSEI: This is really good.

122
00:07:14,916 --> 00:07:16,416
-<i> ...so he can say goodbye.</i>

123
00:07:21,583 --> 00:07:24,458
[Kaori sighs] I can't believe
you're getting me home so late.

124
00:07:24,541 --> 00:07:26,500
- I wanted to call it a night
before, but no.

125
00:07:26,583 --> 00:07:28,583
- We needed that time
to practice.

126
00:07:28,666 --> 00:07:32,333
- [groans] You're right
about it being late, though.

127
00:07:32,416 --> 00:07:34,125
I wonder if your parents
are gonna freak out.

128
00:07:34,208 --> 00:07:35,333
- Would you look at that
up in the sky!

129
00:07:35,416 --> 00:07:38,583
- Focus!
- The stars are so beautiful.

130
00:07:38,666 --> 00:07:40,458
It's like they're
speaking right to us.

131
00:07:40,541 --> 00:07:42,041
- [gasps]

132
00:07:45,958 --> 00:07:46,458
[chuckles]

133
00:07:50,125 --> 00:07:51,291
♪ Twinkle, twinkle ♪

134
00:07:51,375 --> 00:07:54,541
- ♪ Little star ♪
- Huh?

135
00:07:54,625 --> 00:07:58,875
- ♪ How I wonder what you are ♪

136
00:07:58,958 --> 00:08:03,041
BOTH: ♪ Up above
the world so high ♪

137
00:08:03,125 --> 00:08:06,375
♪ Like a diamond in the sky ♪

138
00:08:06,458 --> 00:08:11,875
♪ Twinkle, twinkle,
little star ♪

139
00:08:11,958 --> 00:08:16,666
♪ How I wonder what you are ♪

140
00:08:18,875 --> 00:08:20,208
- It's a pastry shop?

141
00:08:20,291 --> 00:08:22,250
- [entry bell rings]
- I'm home!

142
00:08:22,333 --> 00:08:23,958
Ooh, just wait here for a sec.

143
00:08:24,041 --> 00:08:27,083
- It's fine.
I should probably get going.

144
00:08:27,166 --> 00:08:29,000
- [gasps]
- How dare you

145
00:08:29,083 --> 00:08:31,791
keep my precious daughter
out so late?!

146
00:08:31,875 --> 00:08:33,291
- [whimpers] I'm sorry.
- [roars]

147
00:08:33,375 --> 00:08:35,875
- I'm sorry.
- [growls]

148
00:08:35,958 --> 00:08:38,375
Uh, Arima?
Oh.

149
00:08:38,458 --> 00:08:40,750
- Huh?
- Look who it is, dear.

150
00:08:40,833 --> 00:08:43,750
- Hey, come in! Take a load off!
- [shrieks]

151
00:08:43,833 --> 00:08:45,000
- Eat your fill.

152
00:08:45,083 --> 00:08:46,583
I know how ravenous
you kids get.

153
00:08:46,666 --> 00:08:48,625
- [chuckles] Yes, ma'am.
Thank you very much.

154
00:08:48,708 --> 00:08:49,916
- Oh, what about
the sample items?

155
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:51,041
- Mm-hmm.
- Please, that's okay.

156
00:08:51,125 --> 00:08:52,333
This is more than enough!

157
00:08:52,416 --> 00:08:53,875
- They're big fans of yours,

158
00:08:53,958 --> 00:08:55,416
so good luck stopping 'em.

159
00:08:55,500 --> 00:08:56,625
Back when I was little,

160
00:08:56,708 --> 00:08:58,250
they went to hear you play
a lot.

161
00:08:58,333 --> 00:08:59,916
- You're in big trouble,
young man!

162
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:01,041
- [gasps]

163
00:09:01,125 --> 00:09:02,833
- Cutting your performances
short like that.

164
00:09:02,916 --> 00:09:06,000
Nothing good ever came
from throwing in the towel.

165
00:09:06,083 --> 00:09:09,166
- Mm-hmm. It's like baking
a great spongecake

166
00:09:09,250 --> 00:09:11,500
only to ruin it with too much
frosting in the very last step.

167
00:09:11,583 --> 00:09:14,708
- Mm-hmm.
- Sorry about that.

168
00:09:14,791 --> 00:09:16,625
- That said,
I respect a young man

169
00:09:16,708 --> 00:09:18,416
with the courage
to do his own thing.

170
00:09:18,500 --> 00:09:20,833
- Never let too much frosting
scare you away,

171
00:09:20,916 --> 00:09:22,708
not in baking and not in life.

172
00:09:22,791 --> 00:09:24,791
- I'll keep that in mind.

173
00:09:24,875 --> 00:09:26,208
YOSHIYUKI: Hey!
Want to see some pictures

174
00:09:26,291 --> 00:09:27,791
of Kaori from back
in grade school?!

175
00:09:27,875 --> 00:09:28,583
RYOUKO: Oh, and
the kindergarten pictures!

176
00:09:28,666 --> 00:09:31,625
KAORI: Why do you hate me?!

177
00:09:31,708 --> 00:09:33,166
YOSHIYUKI: In case
you get hungry later.

178
00:09:33,250 --> 00:09:35,291
- Thank you both very much.

179
00:09:35,375 --> 00:09:37,791
I really didn't mean to intrude.

180
00:09:37,875 --> 00:09:40,291
- We'll be at the concert
cheering for the two of you.

181
00:09:40,375 --> 00:09:41,625
- Knock 'em dead.

182
00:09:41,708 --> 00:09:43,666
- Well, then,
I'd better do my best.

183
00:09:43,750 --> 00:09:45,416
- Okay, guys, say good night.

184
00:09:55,416 --> 00:09:57,666
- So that was Kousei Arima.

185
00:09:57,750 --> 00:10:00,125
Seems like a nice kid.
Wouldn't you agree?

186
00:10:00,208 --> 00:10:01,875
- Yeah.

187
00:10:01,958 --> 00:10:06,208
- Why?! Why'd they haul out
pictures of me as a newborn?!

188
00:10:06,291 --> 00:10:08,041
And I was naked!
You saw me naked!

189
00:10:08,125 --> 00:10:09,458
How am I going to live?!

190
00:10:09,541 --> 00:10:11,875
- At least your parents
seem pretty cool.

191
00:10:11,958 --> 00:10:14,041
- Sorry they pushed
all that food on you.

192
00:10:14,125 --> 00:10:15,000
My Mom's got
a soft spot for strays.

193
00:10:15,083 --> 00:10:17,458
- I'm a dog now?

194
00:10:18,833 --> 00:10:20,333
- Hold on.

195
00:10:20,416 --> 00:10:22,000
- [grunts]

196
00:10:22,083 --> 00:10:23,333
Okay.

197
00:10:23,416 --> 00:10:24,333
- Hey, did you get any taller?

198
00:10:24,416 --> 00:10:26,875
- Taller? Not that I know of.

199
00:10:26,958 --> 00:10:29,833
- Maybe it's 'cause you're
not always looking down

200
00:10:29,916 --> 00:10:31,833
at the ground anymore.

201
00:10:31,916 --> 00:10:33,916
Anyway, it sure has been hot.
What's up with that?

202
00:10:35,125 --> 00:10:39,125
KOUSEI:<i> Meaningless small talk.</i>
<i>Familiar scenery.</i>

203
00:10:39,208 --> 00:10:41,291
KAORI: And the humidity.
Ugh! That's the worst part.

204
00:10:41,375 --> 00:10:44,875
Even at night, it's muggy.

205
00:10:44,958 --> 00:10:48,041
KOUSEI:<i> Nothing that stands out</i>
<i>in one's mind. Still...</i>

206
00:10:48,125 --> 00:10:50,416
- But, you know,
I guess summer is worth it

207
00:10:50,500 --> 00:10:51,208
for all the fireworks.

208
00:10:51,291 --> 00:10:52,708
-<i> ...that night...</i>

209
00:10:52,791 --> 00:10:55,916
- [humming "Twinkle,
Twinkle, Little Star"]

210
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:58,208
[laughs]

211
00:10:59,791 --> 00:11:01,625
KOUSEI:<i> I'll remember it always.</i>

212
00:11:03,958 --> 00:11:05,875
[piano and violin
playing "Love's Sorrow"]

213
00:11:09,833 --> 00:11:11,208
- Ugh! What is your problem?!

214
00:11:11,291 --> 00:11:13,791
I told you to make that part
way more legato!

215
00:11:13,875 --> 00:11:16,208
- If I change the dynamics,
the violin gets buried!

216
00:11:16,291 --> 00:11:17,541
Did you think of that, genius?!

217
00:11:17,625 --> 00:11:20,750
- Gotta love summer.
- KOUSEI: You're such a tyrant!

218
00:11:20,833 --> 00:11:23,083
- You bought me
a shaved ice, right?

219
00:11:23,166 --> 00:11:25,125
- Yeah. What do you think
I been eating here?

220
00:11:25,208 --> 00:11:26,833
- [shrieks]
- It's summer, you dumb-ass!

221
00:11:26,916 --> 00:11:28,208
That was my shaved ice,

222
00:11:28,291 --> 00:11:30,375
you monster.
I'm sick of summer school.

223
00:11:30,458 --> 00:11:32,250
I'm just done.
I wanna goof off

224
00:11:32,333 --> 00:11:33,250
and go to a festival...
- Gotta love summer.

225
00:11:33,333 --> 00:11:34,875
- ...watch some fireworks,
you know?

226
00:11:34,958 --> 00:11:36,750
- Yes!
Then you shall have them!

227
00:11:36,833 --> 00:11:37,250
- Hmm?

228
00:11:37,333 --> 00:11:39,416
[Tsubaki laughs]

229
00:11:39,500 --> 00:11:41,125
Now this is summer.
- They're so pretty.

230
00:11:41,208 --> 00:11:43,791
- I hope we don't get caught
sneaking into the pool area

231
00:11:43,875 --> 00:11:47,208
after dark like this.
- Who's gonna find us?

232
00:11:47,291 --> 00:11:49,291
- Yeah, the teachers are all
long gone for the day.

233
00:11:49,375 --> 00:11:51,708
- And refilling the bucket's
gonna be a cinch out here.

234
00:11:53,541 --> 00:11:55,541
- You weren't thinking of
lighting those rockets, right?

235
00:11:55,625 --> 00:11:57,750
- Uh...
- Huh.

236
00:12:00,166 --> 00:12:01,958
[giggles]

237
00:12:02,041 --> 00:12:03,166
-<i> Whoa. She can laugh?</i>

238
00:12:03,250 --> 00:12:04,291
- Aw, man.

239
00:12:04,375 --> 00:12:06,875
This just makes me
dread class even more.

240
00:12:06,958 --> 00:12:08,166
- Hey, you did it to yourself.
- Huh?

241
00:12:08,250 --> 00:12:11,125
- You wouldn't have to go
if you weren't such a moron.

242
00:12:11,208 --> 00:12:12,666
- [groans] Shut up!

243
00:12:12,750 --> 00:12:13,708
You're no genius, either!

244
00:12:13,791 --> 00:12:15,333
- So what are the two of you
gonna do?

245
00:12:15,416 --> 00:12:17,458
- Hmm?
- Huh?

246
00:12:17,541 --> 00:12:18,750
- For high school.

247
00:12:18,833 --> 00:12:20,791
You're not in class
over the break.

248
00:12:20,875 --> 00:12:24,375
Does that mean you guys
are on the music school track?

249
00:12:24,458 --> 00:12:25,916
- Honestly...

250
00:12:31,875 --> 00:12:35,625
I haven't really given
my future any thought.

251
00:12:39,250 --> 00:12:40,958
- [sputters] Uh...

252
00:12:43,833 --> 00:12:46,666
- What I do know
is that me and Friend A

253
00:12:46,750 --> 00:12:48,333
are gonna rock that gala!

254
00:12:48,416 --> 00:12:50,666
The starring role
belongs to us!

255
00:12:50,750 --> 00:12:53,291
Working together,
there's nothing we can't do!

256
00:12:53,375 --> 00:12:55,333
- Attagirl!
That's the spirit!

257
00:12:55,416 --> 00:12:57,708
- [Watari laughs]
- KAORI: Ooh. [laughs]

258
00:12:57,791 --> 00:12:59,541
[both laugh]

259
00:12:59,625 --> 00:13:02,333
- Sparkler party!
- Whoo-hoo! [laughing]

260
00:13:02,416 --> 00:13:03,666
- Ooh! [laughs]

261
00:13:03,750 --> 00:13:05,750
[both laughing]

262
00:13:07,833 --> 00:13:09,041
KOUSEI:<i> Yeah.</i>

263
00:13:09,125 --> 00:13:11,958
<i>Those two look great together.</i>

264
00:13:12,041 --> 00:13:12,875
- KAORI: Careful!
- TSUBAKI: Hmm?

265
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:14,958
- You're gonna
get sparks on me!

266
00:13:15,041 --> 00:13:16,625
- [growls]
What are you staring at?!

267
00:13:16,708 --> 00:13:18,208
- Huh?! Nothing!

268
00:13:20,375 --> 00:13:22,041
- Hah!
- [gasps]

269
00:13:22,125 --> 00:13:23,458
- [sighs]

270
00:13:23,541 --> 00:13:24,791
[girls squeal]

271
00:13:26,208 --> 00:13:27,625
-<i> It's so dark at the bottom.</i>

272
00:13:27,708 --> 00:13:31,041
<i>I can't hear anything.</i>

273
00:13:31,125 --> 00:13:32,375
<i>It feels like...</i>

274
00:13:33,250 --> 00:13:33,750
[memory]<i> Help me.</i>

275
00:13:33,833 --> 00:13:36,333
<i>Please help me.</i>

276
00:13:36,416 --> 00:13:38,541
<i>I can't hear anything.</i>

277
00:13:38,625 --> 00:13:40,250
<i>It's dark. It's dark.</i>

278
00:13:40,333 --> 00:13:43,541
HIROKO:<i> The fact that you</i>
<i>can't hear your own notes,</i>

279
00:13:43,625 --> 00:13:45,041
<i>it just means</i>
<i>you're not limited</i>

280
00:13:45,125 --> 00:13:46,416
<i>to whatever your ears</i>
<i>are picking up.</i>

281
00:13:46,500 --> 00:13:48,541
KOUSEI:<i> Limited to?</i>

282
00:13:48,625 --> 00:13:50,041
<i>What else is there?</i>

283
00:13:50,125 --> 00:13:52,041
-<i> The imagery you carry within.</i>

284
00:13:52,125 --> 00:13:55,916
<i>The sound rising up</i>
<i>from the depths of your soul.</i>

285
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:56,750
<i>The silence you bring</i>
<i>to the table</i>

286
00:13:56,833 --> 00:13:59,375
<i>drowns out everything else,</i>

287
00:13:59,458 --> 00:14:01,125
<i>but your feelings</i>
<i>and memories</i>

288
00:14:01,208 --> 00:14:03,250
<i>and all the sounds</i>
<i>that go with them,</i>

289
00:14:03,333 --> 00:14:05,541
<i>haven't you ever</i>
<i>been able to feel them</i>

290
00:14:05,625 --> 00:14:08,916
<i>soaking into</i>
<i>those muted notes you play?</i>

291
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:10,958
<i>Don't think of it</i>
<i>as a handicap.</i>

292
00:14:11,041 --> 00:14:14,833
<i>Losing your notes,</i>
<i>it might be a gift.</i>

293
00:14:14,916 --> 00:14:16,166
-<i> A gift?</i>

294
00:14:16,250 --> 00:14:17,583
-<i> Cover your ears,</i>

295
00:14:17,666 --> 00:14:19,291
<i>and forget about</i>
<i>what's on the page.</i>

296
00:14:19,375 --> 00:14:22,083
<i>For now, it's enough</i>
<i>that you play what you feel.</i>

297
00:14:22,166 --> 00:14:25,583
<i>I know you've got the chops</i>
<i>to pull that off, at least.</i>

298
00:14:25,666 --> 00:14:28,125
<i>Tracing the sounds within you,</i>

299
00:14:28,208 --> 00:14:30,583
<i>hearing your own</i>
<i>inner landscape,</i>

300
00:14:30,666 --> 00:14:35,333
<i>maybe that's something your Mom</i>
<i>helped prep you for, Kousei.</i>

301
00:14:36,583 --> 00:14:37,458
KAORI:<i> Did you get any taller?</i>

302
00:14:37,541 --> 00:14:39,125
<i>Maybe it's 'cause you're</i>

303
00:14:39,208 --> 00:14:42,125
<i>not always looking down</i>
<i>at the ground anymore.</i>

304
00:14:44,250 --> 00:14:46,458
<i>Now I see you looking up.</i>

305
00:14:46,541 --> 00:14:48,333
[water flowing]

306
00:14:48,416 --> 00:14:53,458
♪♪

307
00:14:53,541 --> 00:14:58,791
