308
00:15:01,666 --> 00:15:03,375
[piano playing "Love's Sorrow"]

309
00:15:03,458 --> 00:15:05,333
[humming melody]

310
00:15:05,416 --> 00:15:12,666
♪♪

311
00:15:12,750 --> 00:15:19,291
♪♪

312
00:15:19,375 --> 00:15:20,333
[humming stops]

313
00:15:20,416 --> 00:15:26,125
[music continues]

314
00:15:26,208 --> 00:15:28,500
- TSUBAKI: Are you all right?!
- WATARI: Kousei!

315
00:15:28,583 --> 00:15:30,666
- Kousei!
- [gasps]

316
00:15:30,750 --> 00:15:32,000
- [groans] Ow. Guh!

317
00:15:32,083 --> 00:15:34,000
- So he's okay?
- Maybe not his head.

318
00:15:34,083 --> 00:15:36,500
- Kousei, you idiot.
- [groans]

319
00:15:36,583 --> 00:15:37,958
- How could you?
- Eh?

320
00:15:38,041 --> 00:15:39,750
- Were you really
gonna go off and drown

321
00:15:39,833 --> 00:15:40,500
in the shallow of a pool?

322
00:15:40,583 --> 00:15:43,000
Everybody would blame me!

323
00:15:43,083 --> 00:15:45,000
- What the hell kind of guy
head-butts you

324
00:15:45,083 --> 00:15:46,875
- after you save his life?
- Kousei.

325
00:15:46,958 --> 00:15:48,500
- [Tsubaki sobbing]
- Eh?

326
00:15:48,583 --> 00:15:50,500
- Huh?
- Huh?

327
00:15:50,583 --> 00:15:53,000
KOUSEI:<i> It's just a pool,</i>

328
00:15:53,083 --> 00:15:55,083
<i>and the moon is out tonight.</i>

329
00:15:56,208 --> 00:15:59,458
<i>But maybe the light</i>
<i>can reach me</i>

330
00:15:59,541 --> 00:16:02,375
<i>at the bottom of my dark ocean</i>

331
00:16:02,458 --> 00:16:04,750
<i>the same way it reached me now.</i>

332
00:16:06,250 --> 00:16:09,541
[insects buzzing]

333
00:16:09,625 --> 00:16:11,375
- Miyazono is playing,
too, right?

334
00:16:11,458 --> 00:16:13,125
- Yeah, with that boy
who stopped in the middle.

335
00:16:13,208 --> 00:16:16,041
They're taking a chance
on that pair.

336
00:16:16,125 --> 00:16:19,083
- I don't know why, but I think
she's gonna pull it off today.

337
00:16:19,166 --> 00:16:20,541
She's something special.

338
00:16:20,625 --> 00:16:22,041
- Nah, she's gonna
drop the ball.

339
00:16:22,125 --> 00:16:25,208
- She's the whole reason
I came to this thing.

340
00:16:25,291 --> 00:16:26,791
[Miike scoffs]

341
00:16:26,875 --> 00:16:28,333
- [laughing]

342
00:16:31,083 --> 00:16:32,375
<i>All right!</i>
<i>I'm totally anonymous!</i>

343
00:16:32,458 --> 00:16:34,625
- Oh, Emi.

344
00:16:34,708 --> 00:16:35,958
- [yelps]

345
00:16:36,041 --> 00:16:37,708
[groans]

346
00:16:37,791 --> 00:16:39,208
- We should go get seated.

347
00:16:39,291 --> 00:16:41,375
- What are you even
doing here, Ms. Ochiai?

348
00:16:41,458 --> 00:16:43,625
I mean, uh, random lady?

349
00:16:43,708 --> 00:16:45,125
- This random lady is the one

350
00:16:45,208 --> 00:16:47,333
who told you Arima
was playing today.

351
00:16:47,416 --> 00:16:49,583
- [gasps]
I don't even remember that.

352
00:16:49,666 --> 00:16:51,583
My coming to this concert
has nothing to do with him.

353
00:16:51,666 --> 00:16:53,333
I'm just here to enjoy
some violin music, honest.

354
00:16:53,416 --> 00:16:56,166
- I grabbed you a program
at the door.

355
00:16:56,250 --> 00:16:58,083
- Uh...
- Come on now.

356
00:16:58,166 --> 00:16:59,708
It should be starting up soon.

357
00:16:59,791 --> 00:17:01,750
-<i> Know-it-all.</i>

358
00:17:01,833 --> 00:17:03,875
[playing "Zigeunerweisen"]

359
00:17:06,166 --> 00:17:08,208
-<i> No judging to be done today.</i>

360
00:17:08,291 --> 00:17:09,750
<i>I can just sit back and enjoy.</i>

361
00:17:09,833 --> 00:17:13,416
<i>- With a lineup this talented,</i>
<i>we're in for quite a treat.</i>

362
00:17:13,500 --> 00:17:18,750
<i>Now then, it's almost time</i>
<i>for my favorite of the bunch.</i>

363
00:17:18,833 --> 00:17:21,166
- Is she trying
to give me a heart attack?!

364
00:17:21,250 --> 00:17:22,583
She's pulling a no-show!

365
00:17:22,666 --> 00:17:24,500
Like Michelangeli
or Pogorelich?!

366
00:17:24,583 --> 00:17:25,541
Yeah, they were pianists,
and she's...

367
00:17:25,625 --> 00:17:27,625
- They've already
gotten started in there.

368
00:17:27,708 --> 00:17:29,791
- No sign of Kaori yet?
- I can't believe she's...

369
00:17:29,875 --> 00:17:31,333
- If this chick
doesn't show up,

370
00:17:31,416 --> 00:17:32,916
like, now,
we are totally screwed.

371
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:34,625
- I've been calling
her cell phone nonstop,

372
00:17:34,708 --> 00:17:36,416
but it keeps sending me
over to voicemail.

373
00:17:36,500 --> 00:17:38,500
[buzzing]

374
00:17:41,375 --> 00:17:43,125
[buzzes echoing]

375
00:17:47,625 --> 00:17:50,458
[insects buzzing]

376
00:17:52,541 --> 00:17:54,666
- What do I do now?
This is a nightmare.

377
00:17:54,750 --> 00:17:56,333
- Let's go backstage
and get you all set, yeah?

378
00:17:56,416 --> 00:17:59,500
That way, you're ready to roll
whenever she gets here.

379
00:17:59,583 --> 00:18:02,625
And as for you, keep calling
until somebody answers it.

380
00:18:02,708 --> 00:18:05,166
- You got it, sister!
- Don't let me down.

381
00:18:05,250 --> 00:18:06,458
- Aye, aye!

382
00:18:06,541 --> 00:18:07,791
TSUBAKI: Best of luck!

383
00:18:09,750 --> 00:18:10,166
[sighs]

384
00:18:14,250 --> 00:18:15,916
- So what's the plan?
- I'll ask 'em

385
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:18,333
if you can take a slot
later on in the concert.

386
00:18:18,416 --> 00:18:19,333
I mean, it's not
a competition today,

387
00:18:19,416 --> 00:18:21,416
so they just
might let it pass.

388
00:18:21,500 --> 00:18:23,708
So long as someone
is willing to trade with you,

389
00:18:23,791 --> 00:18:26,666
we can wait on your partner
'til the last second.

390
00:18:26,750 --> 00:18:28,166
-<i> Kaori.</i>

391
00:18:28,250 --> 00:18:29,833
- If that doesn't pan out,
we're dead in the water.

392
00:18:29,916 --> 00:18:32,666
- You're right. No other choice.

393
00:18:32,750 --> 00:18:34,666
<i>Where are you?</i>

394
00:18:34,750 --> 00:18:36,250
KAORI:<i> It's your call.</i>

395
00:18:36,333 --> 00:18:38,333
<i>I happen to like our song!</i>

396
00:18:38,416 --> 00:18:42,291
<i>- I mean, weren't you</i>
<i>looking forward to this?</i>

397
00:18:42,375 --> 00:18:44,875
<i>I should have never</i>
<i>let her get my hopes up.</i>

398
00:18:44,958 --> 00:18:47,041
[applause]

399
00:18:47,125 --> 00:18:50,375
- It's almost
Kaori Miyazono's turn.

400
00:18:50,458 --> 00:18:52,250
- I wonder what she's gonna do
this time around.

401
00:18:52,333 --> 00:18:55,208
<i>- I haven't been</i>
<i>this excited at a concert</i>

402
00:18:55,291 --> 00:18:56,791
<i>in who know how long.</i>

403
00:18:56,875 --> 00:18:58,958
- You can't just ask me to--
- I'm begging you!

404
00:18:59,041 --> 00:19:01,375
She's gonna roll in here
any minute now! I promise!

405
00:19:01,458 --> 00:19:03,333
- Be that as it may,
I don't have the authority

406
00:19:03,416 --> 00:19:05,916
- to make changes to the--
- What's this all about?

407
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:07,291
STAFF: Oh. Miike.

408
00:19:07,375 --> 00:19:09,041
- I've heard that name before.

409
00:19:09,125 --> 00:19:11,708
Yeah, he's the last kid
in their age group, isn't he?

410
00:19:11,791 --> 00:19:13,625
- Of course. As winner
of the competition,

411
00:19:13,708 --> 00:19:14,750
- he earned that slot--
- Awesome!

412
00:19:14,833 --> 00:19:17,333
So, Miike, need a favor.

413
00:19:17,416 --> 00:19:19,791
Any chance you'd let my pair
play after you today?

414
00:19:19,875 --> 00:19:21,666
Our violinist is running late.
You know how it is.

415
00:19:21,750 --> 00:19:24,083
- Who are you waiting on?

416
00:19:24,166 --> 00:19:26,083
- Her name is Kaori Miyazono,

417
00:19:26,166 --> 00:19:28,250
and I'm sure she'll be here
any minute now.

418
00:19:28,333 --> 00:19:29,541
You'd be doing us
a real solid.

419
00:19:29,625 --> 00:19:32,291
GIRL:<i> Miyazono is playing,</i>
<i>too, right?</i>

420
00:19:32,375 --> 00:19:33,583
WOMAN:<i> She's something special.</i>

421
00:19:33,666 --> 00:19:35,875
- No way.

422
00:19:37,125 --> 00:19:41,125
[sighs] I won,
so I get to go last.

423
00:19:41,208 --> 00:19:42,916
That's my moment to shine.

424
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:44,166
- Right, you are.

425
00:19:44,250 --> 00:19:45,791
Sorry that I asked.

426
00:19:45,875 --> 00:19:48,125
-<i> That is the best time to play.</i>

427
00:19:48,208 --> 00:19:49,583
<i>I don't blame him.</i>

428
00:19:49,666 --> 00:19:50,541
- I hope you understand.

429
00:19:50,625 --> 00:19:53,291
I had to at least
give it a shot.

430
00:19:53,375 --> 00:19:55,458
Okay. Guess we're
canceling after all.

431
00:19:55,541 --> 00:19:56,250
- [Miike sighs]
- KOUSEI: Yeah.

432
00:19:56,333 --> 00:19:58,458
- Well, it's her own fault.

433
00:19:58,541 --> 00:20:01,166
If she really wanted to play,
she wouldn't be late.

434
00:20:01,250 --> 00:20:03,458
I guess she's as undisciplined
in her real life

435
00:20:03,541 --> 00:20:05,416
as she is up onstage
showing off.

436
00:20:05,500 --> 00:20:07,875
The crowd kinda liked her,
and now she thinks

437
00:20:07,958 --> 00:20:08,833
she can breeze in
whenever she feels like.

438
00:20:08,916 --> 00:20:11,125
- Point made. That's enough.

439
00:20:11,208 --> 00:20:13,833
- She's not even a musician.

440
00:20:13,916 --> 00:20:17,000
A musician plays
what the composer wrote down.

441
00:20:17,083 --> 00:20:18,958
When she plays, it's a disaster.

442
00:20:19,041 --> 00:20:21,250
It's just a bunch of noise.

443
00:20:25,083 --> 00:20:27,791
- Who the hell do you think
you are, you smug little brat?!

444
00:20:27,875 --> 00:20:28,916
- No, let him be.
- Uh...

445
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:30,375
- Sorry to have bothered you
on your big day.

446
00:20:30,458 --> 00:20:33,208
- That was wrong of us.
- Don't you bow to him.

447
00:20:33,291 --> 00:20:35,916
He's knocking your partner down.
You need to stick up for her!

448
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:37,625
- You keep your spot.

449
00:20:37,708 --> 00:20:38,625
You'll be the last
middle schooler

450
00:20:38,708 --> 00:20:41,666
they hear today,
just like you wanted.

451
00:20:41,750 --> 00:20:43,458
But know this.

452
00:20:43,541 --> 00:20:44,833
KAORI:<i> The starring role...</i>

453
00:20:46,625 --> 00:20:49,625
- Today, the starring role
belongs to us.

454
00:20:49,708 --> 00:20:53,791
<i>- The promoters' choice</i>
<i>for the junior high division,</i>

455
00:20:53,875 --> 00:20:56,208
<i>Ms. Kaori Miyazono.</i>

456
00:20:56,291 --> 00:20:57,833
- All right.
- Finally, it's Miyazono.

457
00:20:57,916 --> 00:21:01,458
-<i> Wait. So she got here?</i>

458
00:21:01,541 --> 00:21:03,750
[crowd murmuring]

459
00:21:05,416 --> 00:21:08,666
- Huh?
- Isn't he the accompanist?

460
00:21:08,750 --> 00:21:11,000
- Yeah, but where's the violin?

461
00:21:11,083 --> 00:21:13,458
-<i> Arima's playing alone?</i>

462
00:21:13,541 --> 00:21:15,291
-<i> This is blasphemous!</i>

463
00:21:19,375 --> 00:21:20,625
TSUBAKI:<i> Kousei.</i>

